system or something like that.

00:27:10.750 --> 00:27:14.520
But all the ones we've seen,
people try to gain them,

00:27:14.520 --> 00:27:17.130
often successfully.

00:27:17.130 --> 00:27:20.070
Do you have thoughts on what
we can do to combat that?

00:27:20.070 --> 00:27:23.710
JOSHUA KLEIN: So I like to call
this the Friendster effect.

00:27:23.710 --> 00:27:28.210
Which is to say that if you have
a system which is significantly

00:27:28.210 --> 00:27:31.750
gamified, but doesn't
create any extraneous value,

00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:33.460
then it will bankrupt itself.

00:27:33.460 --> 00:27:35.232
So Friendster came
out, everyone's like,

00:27:35.232 --> 00:27:37.190
"Awesome, I can see how
many friends you have."

00:27:37.190 --> 00:27:39.290
It very quickly
became a game where

00:27:39.290 --> 00:27:42.231
everyone tried to
get as many friends

00:27:42.231 --> 00:27:44.230
as they possibly could
as quickly as they could.

00:27:44.230 --> 00:27:45.910
And shortly thereafter,
everyone realized

00:27:45.910 --> 00:27:46.950
that the number of
friends that you had

00:27:46.950 --> 00:27:49.074
didn't indicate anything
except for your dedication

00:27:49.074 --> 00:27:50.716
to Friendster.

00:27:50.716 --> 00:27:52.090
And if you had
that many friends,

00:27:52.090 --> 00:27:54.420
then you were staying
at home very lonely,

00:27:54.420 --> 00:27:56.440
with nobody but
you and Friendster.

00:27:56.440 --> 00:27:59.836
So I think that's one
answer to the question.

00:27:59.836 --> 00:28:01.210
Which is to say,
the systems that

00:28:01.210 --> 00:28:04.460
are only measuring your
influence or your ability

00:28:04.460 --> 00:28:06.070
to interact or
your relative value

00:28:06.070 --> 00:28:08.650
are going to
bankrupt themselves.

00:28:08.650 --> 00:28:11.390
The second element to
it is that, as people

00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:14.730
get invested in these accounts
through participation,

00:28:14.730 --> 00:28:18.040
whether that be the community,
like on Stack Overflow,

00:28:18.040 --> 00:28:21.580
or exchange of goods or
services like on eBay,

00:28:21.580 --> 00:28:24.350
those accounts acquire value.

00:28:24.350 --> 00:28:26.670
And if you make that value
somewhat transportable,

00:28:26.670 --> 00:28:28.390
it just exacerbates the effect.

00:28:28.390 --> 00:28:30.400
So if I can use my
eBay seller rating

00:28:30.400 --> 00:28:34.536
to then go sell on another
platform or to get a loan,

00:28:34.536 --> 00:28:36.910
there are systems that will
check your eBay seller rating

00:28:36.910 --> 00:28:39.620
and then instantly give
you a loan based on that.

00:28:39.620 --> 00:28:43.910
I think you'll see people
adhering to them longer.

00:28:43.910 --> 00:28:46.200
And I understand that
it's context-dependent.

00:28:46.200 --> 00:28:48.000
In this case, a
seller-buyer relationship.

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:49.750
But I think that that
answers a little bit

00:28:49.750 --> 00:28:52.520
of the question of
how portable they are.

00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:54.985
Does that address the question?

00:28:54.985 --> 00:28:56.360
AUDIENCE: That's
one answer, yes.

00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:58.280
JOSHUA KLEIN: That's
